<TITLE> OMS of rice resumes countrywide </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 20 (bdnews24.com)Open Market Sales of rice resumed Wednesday, with a target of serving 14 lakh people a day. Mollah Waheduzzaman, secretary to the ministry of food and disaster management inaugurated the OMS programme at Palashi market. P Costa, director general of the food directorate told bdnews24.com Tuesday: "This time rice will be sold under OMS for 59 consecutive days over August, September and October." OMS shops will remain open six days a week, except Fridays. One kilo of rice will be priced at Tk 28. An individual may purchase up to three kilogrammes of rice each day under the programme. "Two lakh and 51 thousand tonnes of rice have been allocated for 14 lakh people per day," said Costa. "Whether allocation will increase will depend on demand." Rice will be sold across the country through 7,141 dealers. Dealers in six city corporations, Narayanganj, Narsingdi and Gazipur will be allocated 765kgs to sell each day, while dealers in other areas will get a total of 510kgs to sell per day. Dhaka city alone will see some 945 OMS dealers, including 25 trucks. Costa said about 2.5 lakh tonnes of rice were sold in open markets earlier this year between March and May. bdnews
